He had no word for them but “Ye do greatly err; the kingdom shall be taken from you'' ; and they no earnestness to bring to him except that of fear for their own safety‚ which struck the murderous blow. Their conservatism in religion was of no more use than death is of use to life. It was not even in that stage of decom- position which gives enrichment to the roots of a new life, as Pharisaism was. It was the death of salt without savour, of a lamp that holds no oil.

The defect of conservatism is failure to see that the past must continually be sacrificed for the higher future. The virtue of conservatism is to acerete the faith of the dead ; its vice is to have no faith in the God of the living.
